---
import Layout from '../../components/Layout.astro';
import FoilTemplate from '../../components/FoilTemplate.astro';

const body = `[YOUR DATE]

[YOUR NAME]
[YOUR ADDRESS]
[YOUR EMAIL]

Records Access Officer
[DISTRICT NAME]
[DISTRICT ADDRESS]

Re: Freedom of Information Law request — 1:1 device program policy and contracts

Dear Records Access Officer:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law (Public Officers Law Article 6), I request copies of the following records relating to the district's 1:1 student device program:

1. The current Board of Education policy or policies governing the district's 1:1 device program, including any policies on take-home use, acceptable use (AUP), parent/student device agreements, lost or damaged device fees, and consequences for non-participation.

2. The full text of any signed contracts and master agreements between the district and the device manufacturer(s) and software vendor(s) used in the 1:1 program (e.g., Google, Apple, Microsoft, the device leasing or financing entity, and any classroom-management or monitoring software vendors).

3. Any current vendor or product list identifying every application, extension, or service installed by default on student-issued devices in grades K-5.

4. Any board or administrative policy describing a parent's options to (a) decline a take-home device, (b) opt the student out of specific applications, or (c) request alternatives to device-based instruction.

5. Board minutes from any meetings in the past 24 months in which the 1:1 device program, its renewal, or its modification was discussed or voted on.

I request electronic delivery (PDF or original electronic format) where possible, to my email address above. Please advise in advance if any portion of this request will incur fees over $5.

If any portion of this request is denied, please cite the specific statutory exemption relied on, and please provide the records that are not subject to that exemption.

Please acknowledge this request within five business days as required by §89(3) of the Public Officers Law.

Thank you for your assistance.

Sincerely,

[YOUR NAME]`;
---

<Layout title="FOIL — 1:1 device policy and contracts">
  <article class="prose-measure mx-auto px-4 py-10">
    <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mb-1"><a href="/foil/">← All FOIL templates</a></p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-2">FOIL: 1:1 device policy and contracts</h1>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-6 mb-1">What this gets you</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-700">The board policy that governs the 1:1 program, the actual signed contracts behind it, and the list of software installed by default. This is the foundational request — the document trail every other §2-d question rests on.</p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-6 mb-1">Where to send it</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-700">The district's Records Access Officer (RAO) — usually the district clerk. Look on the district website under "Board of Education," "FOIL," "Records Access," or "District Clerk."</p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-6 mb-1">What to expect</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-stone-700">
      <li>5 business days to acknowledge.</li>
      <li>20 business days to respond, deny, or specify a reasonable later date.</li>
      <li>If denied, written reasons; you have 30 days to appeal.</li>
    </ul>

    <FoilTemplate
      title="Template letter"
      description="Replace bracketed fields. Email is fine; address it to the Records Access Officer."
      body={body}
    />

    <div class="disclaimer mt-8">
      Template, not legal advice. For appeals or contested denials, an education attorney can help.
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
